c energy dissipation of the\nAUSM$^{+}$-up solver already converges at a lower resolution compared to\nAUSM$^{+}_{\\mathrm{B}}$ -up. The extracted entrainment rates at the boundaries\nof the convection zone are well represented by the bulk Richardson entrainment\nlaw and the corresponding fitting parameters are in agreement with published\nresults for carbon shell burning.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Jul 2021 18:03:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-08"}
